# Doublecheck

When invoked, run a three-layer verification pipeline on AI-generated output. Extract claims, find sources, flag hallucination patterns. The user decides what is true.

## Activation

- "use doublecheck": persistent mode. Respond: "**Doublecheck is now active.** I'll verify factual claims in my responses. Say 'full report' for detailed verification. Turn off with 'turn off doublecheck.'"
- "doublecheck this: [text]": one-shot full verification
- "turn off doublecheck": deactivate

## Active Mode

Classify responses:

| Type | Action |
|------|--------|
| Analysis/guidance where errors carry real consequences | Full report |
| Document/data summary | Inline verification |
| Code/creative/casual | Skip |

### Inline Format

After response, add:

---
**Verification (N claims checked)**
- [VERIFIED] "Claim" -- Source: [URL]
- [PLAUSIBLE] "Claim" -- no source found
- [FABRICATION RISK] "Claim" -- citation not found
_Say "full report" for detailed verification._

### Auto-Escalation

If ANY claim is DISPUTED or FABRICATION RISK: add "**Heads up:** [problem]" at top, produce full report instead of inline.

## Pipeline

**Layer 1 -- Self-Audit:** Extract claims (C1, C2...). Types: Factual, Statistical, Citation, Entity, Causal, Temporal. Check internal consistency.

**Layer 2 -- Source Verification:** Search for each claim. Provide URLs. Citations: if exact reference not found, flag FABRICATION RISK.

**Layer 3 -- Adversarial Review:** Assume errors. Check for: fabricated citations, unsourced statistics, confident specificity on uncertain topics, plausible-but-wrong associations, temporal confusion, overgeneralization, missing qualifiers.

## Ratings

VERIFIED (source found) | PLAUSIBLE (general knowledge) | UNVERIFIED (no evidence) | DISPUTED (contradicting source) | FABRICATION RISK (hallucination pattern)

## Report

Summary > Flagged Items (DISPUTED/FABRICATION RISK first) > All Claims by rating > Internal Consistency > What Was Not Checked > Limitations

## Limitations (always disclose)

- Same model, same biases
- Web search misses paywalled/recent content
- VERIFIED means "source found," not "definitely correct"
